cff-version: 1.2.0
message: "If you use Paper-WorkFlow in your research workflow, please cite it as below."
title: "Paper-WorkFlow: an end-to-end meta-orchestrator for empirical economics & social-science papers"
abstract: >-
  Paper-WorkFlow is a Claude Code skill that orchestrates the full empirical-paper
  pipeline (topic → design → data → identification & estimation → method gate →
  exhibits → drafting → polishing → de-AI → draft-quality gate → simulated review &
  revision → journal selection & submission → replication handoff) as a 10-stage,
  twin-gate, resumable pipeline. It does not re-implement sub-skills; it routes to
  existing skills and dispatches context-protected subagents at the right human
  decision points, with research-grade credibility layers (method gate, design-risk
  ledger, sample/estimand audit, claim-integrity audit, and citation-existence /
  temporal-integrity checks).
type: software
authors:
